meta {
  name: Channel Message Send
  type: http
  seq: 5
}

post {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/chat/channels/{{channelId}}/messages/
  body: json
  auth: inherit
}

headers {
  X-Workspace-Id: {{workspaceId}}
  Content-Type: application/json
}

body:json {
  {
    "body": "Summarize my inbox this month",
    "client_msg_id": ""
  }
}

docs {
  Same code path as the WS ``send_message`` action. The persisted
  message is fanned out to every WS subscriber of
  ``chat-channel-{id}`` via ``channel_layer.group_send``.
  
  --- Agent dispatch (A1, 2026-06-15) ---
  After the row commits, ``transaction.on_commit`` calls
  ``maybe_dispatch_agent(message)``. If the channel has an
  ``AgentSession`` attached AND (it's a DM OR @donna mentioned),
  a Celery ``run_agent_turn`` task fires.
  
  The agent calls cortex tools (cortex_query / read_entity /
  get_context / prepare_context), composes an answer, and persists
  it as a NEW Message with ``author_agent`` set.
  
  --- Polling for the reply ---
  Use "Channel Messages List" right after — the latest message
  with ``author_agent`` set is Donna's reply. Typical latency:
  1–5s (depends on tool count + LLM speed).
  
  --- AgentSession setup (one-time per channel) ---
  Bruno has no AgentSession endpoint. Once per workspace, in the
  Django shell:
  
    from donna.chat.models import Channel, AgentSession
    ch = Channel.objects.get(id="<channel-uuid>")
    AgentSession.objects.create(channel=ch, name="Donna")
  
  After that, every message in that DM triggers Donna.
}
